# Test commands (agents)

On Windows, `vendor\bin\phpunit` has no `.exe` extension. Invoking it directly opens a "choose app" dialog instead of running tests.

**Never** use `vendor/bin/phpunit` or `vendor\bin\phpunit` in shell commands.

**Always** use one of:

| Context | Command |
|---------|---------|
| Recommended (Windows) | `.\scripts\test.ps1` — auto Docker if local PHP &lt; 8.2 |
| Single test file | `.\scripts\test.ps1 tests/Unit/SomeTest.php` |
| Local PHP 8.2+ | `composer test` or `composer test -- tests/Unit/SomeTest.php` |
| Docker (PHP 8.2, CI parity) | `docker compose --profile tools run --rm php-test vendor/bin/phpunit` |
| Full composer check in Docker | `docker compose --profile tools run --rm composer check` |

`scripts/test.ps1` picks local `composer test` when PHP ≥ 8.2, otherwise `php-test` (php:8.2-cli). Same codebase via volume mount.

See `docs/PHP_INSTALL_WINDOWS.md` and `docs/DEVELOPER.md` for humans.
